# UI Components and Styling

Open Filmly uses a UI component library with TailwindCSS for styling.

## Core UI Components
- [src/components/ui/button.tsx](mdc:src/components/ui/button.tsx) - Button component
- [src/components/ui/card.tsx](mdc:src/components/ui/card.tsx) - Card component
- [src/components/ui/dialog.tsx](mdc:src/components/ui/dialog.tsx) - Dialog/Modal component
- [src/components/ui/input.tsx](mdc:src/components/ui/input.tsx) - Input component
- [src/components/ui/tabs.tsx](mdc:src/components/ui/tabs.tsx) - Tabs component

## Media-Specific Components
- [src/components/media-card.tsx](mdc:src/components/media-card.tsx) - Card for displaying media items
- [src/components/media-grid.tsx](mdc:src/components/media-grid.tsx) - Grid layout for media items
- [src/components/Movies.tsx](mdc:src/components/Movies.tsx) - Movies view component

## Styling Configuration
- [tailwind.config.ts](mdc:tailwind.config.ts) - TailwindCSS configuration
- [src/app/globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css) - Global CSS styles

Always follow the existing component patterns when creating new UI elements.
